b. Based on the evaluation reports of the MSWDO, determine from the list of recipients who among them are found to have misappropriated the grant and submit the list to the Accounting Unit, which list shall be the basis on retaining the receivable amount in the books. However, the Accounting Units should reclassify the same into the appropriate receivable account considering that the barangay governments of Aroroy were not the recipients of the said livelihood assistance; and
c. Upon said determination, prepare the necessary adjustments in the books to correct the error. Likewise, prepare and maintain subsidiary ledgers in accordance with Section 64, Volume I, Government Auditing and Accounting Manual.

