b. Speed up the implementation of priority development projects and programs as embodied in the AIP to attain the socio-economic development and environmental management outcomes for the constituents' benefits; and,
c. Also, make representation to the Sangguniang Bayan to revert to surplus the unutilized and the unobligated balances/savings of prior year’s projects and use the amount for other LGU projects that need immediate attention,

We recommended Management’s strict adherence to the accounting and reporting guidelines for the Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Fund (LDRRMF) set forth in COA Circular No. 2012-002; with emphasis on the following:
1. The Municipal Budget Officer (MBO) should see to it that in the preparation of the budget proposal for the ensuing year, the approved LDRRMFIP unexpended balance of the MF-CO for the previous year should be forwarded and made as continuing appropriation, retained as to amount and specific program or project. When asked as to the basis of said continuing appropriation, the previous LDRRMFIP/s shall be presented showing the portion of projects for capital outlays. While the report/data on the unexpended balance of QRF and MF-MOOE for the current year shall be forwarded to the Accounting Office at the end of the year for appropriate action to transfer said amount to the Special Trust Fund;
2. The Municipal Accountant, in drawing the disbursement voucher to effect the transfer, should properly validate and verify the correctness of the unexpended balance by the MBO to ensure that there would be no excess or insufficiency of fund transfer. The unexpended balances of QRF and MF-MOOE at year end, lodged in the Special Trust Fund and specifically segregated into the year it was obtained, shall be reported and communicated to the LDRRMO for the preparation of the Investment Plan;
3. The LDRRMO shall prepare two (2) LDRRMFIP composed of the plan for the current year to be forwarded to the MBO and for the previous years’ unexpended balance of QRF and MF-MOOE based on the report received from the Accounting Office. Both reports should present the preparedness and mitigation projects classified under the program for DRRM and under the functional classification of the implementing office using the project breakdown and codes indicated in COA Circular No. 2012-001. The LDRRMFIP in a separate caption for the unexpended previous years’ balances in the Special Trust Fund shall be reviewed and updated annually;
4. RAAO and subsidiary ledgers should be regularly and properly prepared by source and by year to be used as basis for the Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRMF; and
All concerned offices should accordingly coordinate to ensure the reliability of their respective reports.

1. The Municipal Accountant should ensure that the unexpended balance of QRF and MF-MOOE for each year be timely transferred at year-end;
2. The excessive amount of P2,712,203.86 pertaining to the unexpended LDRRMF of CY 2014 should be appropriately reverted back to the General Fund;
3. The Accounting Office should coordinate with the Budget Office to reconcile their records and obtain the correct amount of the unexpended balances; and
4. The Unexpended MF-MOOE of prior years (2011-2014) reflected in the continuing appropriation per CY 2015 SAAOB amounting to P1,839,088.63 should be immediately transferred to the Special Trust Fund.
